## User Experience Flow
1. User navigates to the Terms of Service page from the footer or legal section.
2. Page loads the latest Terms content, showing:
   - Title and Effective Date
   - Table of Contents with anchors
   - Content sections (Usage, Prohibited Actions, IP, Liability, Service Levels, Modifications, Termination, Contact)
3. User reads content; can scroll with a highlighted TOC reflecting the current section.
4. User may click Export to PDF:
   - Frontend calls the PDF export endpoint.
   - Server renders the PDF; user receives a download prompt or in-app PDF viewer.
5. Admin/legal user edits content:
   - Create a new version via CMS or API.
   - Publish; new version metadata updates EffectiveDate and LastUpdated.
   - All users see the latest version automatically.

