## Technical Specifications

Data Models: 
- LegalDocument
  - id: string (uuid)
  - name: string
  - version: int
  - effectiveDate: date
  - lastUpdated: date
  - sections: Section[]
  - brandingMeta: { companyName: string, logoUrl?: string }
- Section
  - id: string
  - title: string
  - contentBlocks: ContentBlock[]
- ContentBlock
  - type: string (paragraph|list|subheading|link|blockquote)
  - content: string
  - bulletPoints?: string[]
  - links?: Link[]
- Link
  - text: string
  - href: string

API Endpoints:
- GET /legal/terms/latest -> LegalDocument (id, version, effectiveDate, sections)
- GET /legal/templates/{name} -> Template content for privacy/terms
- POST /legal/documents/{id}/versions -> Create new version; body includes updated sections
- GET /legal/documents/{id}/export/pdf -> binary application/pdf

Security:
- Authentication: Admin/Legal roles required for version creation and template updates. Public GET for latest Terms (read-only).
- Authorization: Enforce access control on versioning endpoints.
- Data integrity: Validate version increments; ensure effectiveDate <= lastUpdated ≤ now.
- Data privacy: No sensitive user data in document content.

Validation:
- Content validation: Each section must have title; contentBlocks must have valid types; lists must have at least one bulletPoint when type is list.
- URL validation for links.
- Date validation for effectiveDate and lastUpdated.
- PDF export should succeed for valid document IDs; handle errors gracefully.

