  - Title, effective date, and last updated date.
  - Table of Contents with working anchors and active-section highlighting on scroll.
  - All content sections rendered from structured data; supports lists, links, and subheadings.
  - Print/Export to PDF functionality producing a properly formatted document with header/footer and page numbers.
- [ ] The UI adheres to the defined visual style (colors, typography, spacing, and card/shadow usage) and is accessible (WCAG 2.1 AA).
- [ ] Content management: Admin can create a new version; versioning metadata updates correctly (version number increments, effectiveDate and lastUpdated reflect changes).
- [ ] Internationalization readiness: Strings plumbed via locale keys; layout accommodates translations without breaking layout (RTL support not required immediately but future-proofed).
- [ ] No external API dependencies required for the page rendering; content comes from the internal legal document store.

